article.headline: Colonials beat No. 20 Temple in turnover-filled game
article.linkText: Colonials beat No. 20 Temple in turnover-filled game
article.story:
WASHINGTON (AP) -- Freshman forward Jazmine Adair scored 11
points, and George Washington beat Temple 58-41 Wednesday
night in a game in which both teams had more turnovers than field
goals.

Adair set career-highs with 11 rebounds and three blocks and
helped limit Temple's Lady Comfort, who was shooting 70 percent for
the season entering the game, to six points on 2-for-8 shooting.

The game featured the only two remaining unbeaten teams in
Atlantic 10 conference play, but George Washington (10-4, 3-0)
committed 21 turnovers and made 20 field goals. Temple (10-4, 2-1)
had 19 turnovers, 17 field goals and shot 23 percent.

Kimberly Beck and Sarah-Jo Lawrence scored 10 points apiece for
the Colonials, who have won four straight. Khadija Bowens led
Temple (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No, 19 AP) with 11 points.

The Owls lead 8-2 early, then scored only two points over the
next 13:54. The Colonials' had first-half runs of 6-0 and 11-0 and
took the lead for good at 12-10. They led 25-15 at halftime.

The Owls cut the lead to six with 11:26 to go in the game, but
Adair scored twice in a 10-0 run that put the Colonials back in
control.
